<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1724,2001]" pageId="3" pageNumber="246">Body creamy white to pale ochreous. Vertex occasionally tinged with pale orange centrally. Fore wing ivory white, often with longitudinal pale brown stripes on clavus and vein CuA.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1724,2001]" pageId="3" pageNumber="246">
Female 
<number box="[290,303,1796,1821]" pageId="3" pageNumber="246" value="7.0">7</number>
th abdominal sternite trapezoidal, with posterior margin swollen near middle and bearing numerous short hairs posteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1724,2001]" box="[199,1021,1868,1893]" pageId="3" pageNumber="246">
Body length (mean): ♂, 
<quantity box="[473,608,1868,1892]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="246" unit="mm" value="2.95" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.8">2.8–3.1 mm</quantity>
(3.0 mm); ♀, 
<quantity box="[768,903,1868,1892]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="246" unit="mm" value="3.05" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.9">2.9–3.2 mm</quantity>
(3.0 mm).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1724,2001]" pageId="3" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,1903,1928]" pageId="3" pageNumber="246">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with dorsal process curved inward and bifurcated near apex. Aedeagus arcuate, with pair of apical processes and ventral process; apical process long and thin, 
<number box="[988,1072,1940,1965]" pageId="3" pageNumber="246" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.5</number>
times as long as aedeagal shaft; ventral process, 
<number box="[333,417,1976,2001]" pageId="3" pageNumber="246" value="0.6499999999999999" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.7</number>
times as long as aedeagal shaft; preatrium long; gonopore subapical on ventral surface.
</paragraph>
