<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="248" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="248">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,404,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="248">Remarks.</emphasis>
A detailed description of this species was provided by Chiang &amp; Knight (
<number box="[1204,1264,404,428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="248" value="1990.0">1990</number>
), but Japanese specimens have a slight difference in the male genitalia: the pygofer process is bifurcated apically. Morphological features of female 
<number box="[366,379,476,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="248" value="7.0">7</number>
th abdominal sternite are described here for the first time. This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura, 1932" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1932" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Zygina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="akazu">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="248">A. akazu</emphasis>
(Matsumura, 
<number box="[386,446,512,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="248" value="1932.0">1932</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but it is distinguishable by a character of male genitalia: pair of aedeagal apical processes remarkably longer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="248">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,583,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="248">Bionomics.</emphasis>
The host plants are 
<taxonomicName box="[609,850,584,608]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Macaranga" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="248" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tanarius">
<emphasis box="[609,850,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="248">Macaranga tanarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Muell.-Arg. (
<taxonomicName box="[1086,1256,583,608]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="248" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Euphorbiaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Link) C.B. Rob." authorityName="(Link) C.B. Rob." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pipturus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="248" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arborescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="248">Pipturus arborescens</emphasis>
(Link) C.B. Rob.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[499,626,620,645]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="248" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Urticaceae</taxonomicName>
). This species seems to occur throughout the year.
</paragraph>
